WEBVTT

00:08.950 --> 00:10.718
You're joining the Army?

00:10.795 --> 00:12.002
I'm a translator.

00:12.079 --> 00:13.429
I won't see any combat.

00:14.632 --> 00:15.740
Asako-san!

00:15.742 --> 00:18.392
Henry-san, he's here!

00:18.469 --> 00:21.044
I brought you some warm water
to soak your hands and feet.

00:22.457 --> 00:23.664
She's just trying to help!

00:25.126 --> 00:28.243
I never used to believe in
that old-country stuff.

00:28.245 --> 00:30.646
Yurei be anywhere
you go.

00:30.723 --> 00:32.555
It follow you.

00:40.064 --> 00:41.991
<i>"Dear Luz,</i>

00:41.993 --> 00:43.734
<i>It's 3:00 a.m.
here in Guadalcanal,</i>

00:43.736 --> 00:46.587
<i>and I'm wide awake.</i>

00:46.589 --> 00:49.815
<i>You'll be glad to hear
I'm far from the action...</i>

00:49.817 --> 00:52.334
<i>so far that Colonel Stallings
hasn't even told</i>

00:52.336 --> 00:55.912
<i>the Marine officers
about us yet.</i>

00:55.914 --> 01:00.159
<i>Something about
keeping morale up.</i>

01:00.161 --> 01:02.937
<i>My bunkmate is Arthur Ogawa,</i>

01:02.939 --> 01:04.421
<i>and we spend all day
in our tent</i>

01:04.423 --> 01:07.650
<i>translating documents
and fighting off malaria...</i>

01:10.672 --> 01:12.280
<i>but for the life of me,</i>

01:12.282 --> 01:15.766
<i>I don't know why
I can't fall asleep.</i>

01:18.346 --> 01:20.029
<i>Six nights in a row,</i>

01:20.031 --> 01:21.530
<i>every time I drift off,</i>

01:21.532 --> 01:25.701
<i>I feel like the enemy
is closing in on me.</i>

01:25.703 --> 01:29.688
<i>That's when I think of you.</i>

01:29.690 --> 01:32.207
<i>I'm not saying it's better
back at camp,</i>

01:32.209 --> 01:35.436
<i>but at least I imagine
it's calmer.</i>

01:35.438 --> 01:38.364
<i>After Yoshida-san
and Furuya-san,</i>

01:38.366 --> 01:40.433
<i>it better be.</i>

01:42.053 --> 01:44.778
<i>I bought me a new camera
in Australia,</i>

01:44.780 --> 01:46.397
<i>so expect some pictures soon."</i>

